column2: Professional Development provided for Teachers\r\rMeasure2017-182018-192019-20\rNumber of school days dedicated to Staff Development and Continuous Improvement8710\r\rAll curriculum and instructional improvement activities at Santa Ana Unified School District are aligned to the new Common Core State Standards. Staff\rdevelopment concentrations are selected and identified based on student assessment results
column5: and professional\rdevelopment surveys.\r\rAll staff development activities at the Santa Ana Unified School District are focused on increasing student learning and proficiency. During the 2019-20\rschool year
column6: our school-sponsored three days of staff development. Staff training topics at Monroe included: Dual Language Immersion
column20: Arts Education.\r\rSanta Ana Unified School District offers supplemental training and support for new and ongoing program implementation. Training activities take place\rthroughout the school year
column22: and during the summer and generally focus on curriculum

column25: district training opportunities focused on the following:\r•\rDual Language\r•\rAcademic Discourse\r•\rPBIS\r•\rCASPP interim Assessments\r•\rPLTW STEAM Project Lead the Way\r•\rDifferentiated Instruction\r•\rGifted and Talented Education\r•\rWorking with Parents\r•\rSpecial Education\r•\rData Analysis and Using Data to Drive Instruction\r•\rAVID Strategies\r•\rStudent Engagement Strategies\r•\rSIPPS Program\r•\rEnglish Language Development\r•\rIrvine Math Project\r•\rCalifornia Math Expressions\r•\rAdvanced Benchmark\r•\rELPAC\r\rNew teachers are supported by peer coaching and extensive staff development. The TIPS Induction Program (Teacher Induction and Professional Support)\ris a state-approved program that offers additional support and assistance to newly credentialed teachers. All new teachers are assigned to a Support\rProvider (mentor teacher) and provided individualized support over a two-year period. More information about the TIPS Induction Program is available\ron http://www.sausdtips.org/.\r\rTo support veteran teachers as well as new teachers to the district
column26: Santa Ana Unified School District offers Peer Assistance and Review (PAR) which is\reasily defined as teachers helping teachers. Experienced and knowledgeable veteran teachers
